      • VARINT_LENGTH_MASKS

        private static final long[] VARINT_LENGTH_MASKS
        The first byte of a variable-length integer (varint) will have one of these bit masks indicating the total length in bytes.

        0x80 is a one-byte integer, 0x40 is two bytes, and so on up to eight bytes.

      • readUnsignedVarint

        public long readUnsignedVarint(ExtractorInput input,
                               boolean allowEndOfInput,
                               boolean removeLengthMask,
                               int maximumAllowedLength)
                        throws java.io.IOException,
                               java.lang.InterruptedException
        Reads an EBML variable-length integer (varint) from an ExtractorInput such that reading can be resumed later if an error occurs having read only some of it.

        If an value is successfully read, then the reader will automatically reset itself ready to read another value.

        If an IOException or InterruptedException is throw, the read can be resumed later by calling this method again, passing an ExtractorInput providing data starting where the previous one left off.

        Parameters:
        input - The ExtractorInput from which the integer should be read.
        allowEndOfInput - True if encountering the end of the input having read no data is allowed, and should result in C.RESULT_END_OF_INPUT being returned. False if it should be considered an error, causing an EOFException to be thrown.
        removeLengthMask - Removes the variable-length integer length mask from the value.
        maximumAllowedLength - Maximum allowed length of the variable integer to be read.
        Returns:
        The read value, or C.RESULT_END_OF_INPUT if allowEndOfStream is true and the end of the input was encountered, or C.RESULT_MAX_LENGTH_EXCEEDED if the length of the varint exceeded maximumAllowedLength.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If an error occurs reading from the input.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted.
